# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# mvp_api environment variables — example/template
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This file documents env vars mvp_api reads. Copy values into the project-
# root `.env` (which mvp_api's `bun run --env-file ../../.env` loads at dev
# time). Production values live in Vercel project settings, not here.
#
# See docs/superpowers/specs/2026-05-03-cloud-offload-architecture.md (D24)
# and docs/superpowers/specs/2026-05-03-c3.5-local-dev-transport.md for the
# lambda-invoker design.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Lambda invoker (added in C3.5) ─────────────────────────────────────────
# When USE_LOCAL_ENVIRONMENT is "true", apps/mvp_api/src/lib/lambda-invoker.ts
# routes invoke()/enqueue() calls to localhost HTTP servers (each Lambda's
# server.py running natively via `uv run python -m <pkg>.server`).
# When unset/false, it uses AWS SDK Lambda invoke (sync; wired at C4) or
# SQS publish (async; wired at C7).
USE_LOCAL_ENVIRONMENT=true

# Per-Lambda local URL overrides (optional). Defaults are
# http://localhost:<port> per the table in python/lambdas/README.md.
#
# Smoketest (C3.5 throwaway; deleted at C4):
# LOCAL_SMOKETEST_LAMBDA_URL=http://localhost:4100
#
# Future Lambdas — uncomment as the corresponding row lands:
# LOCAL_PARSE_KMZ_LAMBDA_URL=http://localhost:4101         # added at C4
# LOCAL_COMPUTE_LAYOUT_LAMBDA_URL=http://localhost:4102    # added at C6
# LOCAL_DETECT_WATER_LAMBDA_URL=http://localhost:4103      # added at C16
# LOCAL_COMPUTE_ENERGY_LAMBDA_URL=http://localhost:4104    # added at C18
